name: 23S rRNA pseudouridine1911/1915/1917 synthase
comment: Pseudouridine synthase RluD converts uridines at positions 1911, 1915, and 1917 of 23S rRNA to pseudouridines. These nucleotides are located in the functionally important helix-loop 69 of 23S rRNA [1].

references.title: Substrate specificity of the pseudouridine synthase RluD in Escherichia coli.
Pseudouridylation of helix 69 of 23S rRNA is necessary for an effective translation termination.
references.journal: Proc. Natl. Acad. Sci. U. S. A. 104 (2007) 19410-5.

references.title: Crystal structure of the RluD pseudouridine synthase catalytic module, an enzyme that modifies 23S rRNA and is essential for normal cell growth of Escherichia coli.
Isolation and properties of Escherichia coli 23S-RNA pseudouridine 1911, 1915, 1917 synthase (RluD).
